    "historicalContext": "Austria was the first read on Cadillac's major sidepod/bodywork/floor upgrade: Bottas' P13 in FP1 suggested the package had moved the MAC-26 forward, but Pérez then lost most of Friday to electrical shutdowns and Bottas' FP2 was cut short by a mechanical overheating issue. Qualifying turned that mixed practice signal into a still-incomplete step — Pérez P19 and Bottas P20 were almost a second clear of Aston Martin, yet the lead Cadillac remained 0.436s behind Albon's Williams and 1.051s from the Q2 cut on the Red Bull Ring's short lap.",
